headline: Why Western Digital (WDC) Stock Is Up Today
summary: Shares of leading data storage manufacturer Western Digital (NASDAQ: WDC) jumped 9.9% in the afternoon session after the company posted strong fourth-quarter fiscal 2025 results that beat Wall Street estimates. The company's revenue jumped 30% year-over-year to $2.61 billion, while its earnings per share reached $1.66.
